This paper deals with a query processing system for computing the moving k nearest neighbor (MkNN) query in both two-dimensional Euclidean space and road networks. The paper discusses a novel algorithm called the Influential Neighbor Set (INS) algorithm, which uses a small set of safe guarding objects instead of safe regions to achieve high overall query processing efficiency. This work involves database systems (cs.DB) as it deals with query processing, data structures (cs.DS) as it discusses algorithms for efficient computation, artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves machine learning techniques for computing nearest neighbors, computational geometry (cs.GR) as it deals with geometric algorithms, and social and information networks (cs.SI) as it involves processing queries on road networks.
